WEBVTT

00:01.134 --> 00:04.071
[♪ ethereal music playing]

00:09.009 --> 00:10.244
[KENJAKU] I'm sorry.

00:11.879 --> 00:12.813
Who are you?

00:13.513 --> 00:16.450
[KENJAKU] The sorcerer
who erected the barrier here.

00:17.017 --> 00:18.819
This spot has been chosen

00:19.253 --> 00:21.221
for people
to kill each other in.

00:21.755 --> 00:25.659
Unfortunately,
there's no real honor in it.

00:26.660 --> 00:27.794
Kill each other?

00:29.596 --> 00:31.665
Could you possibly find
another neighborhood

00:31.765 --> 00:32.866
to do that in, please?

00:33.734 --> 00:37.671
[laughs] I didn't realize
you were such a funny kid.

00:38.572 --> 00:41.608
There's an old execution site
not too far from here.

00:41.708 --> 00:43.911
It serves as the center
of the barrier.

00:44.311 --> 00:46.880
It covers a five
or six-kilometer radius.

00:47.381 --> 00:50.117
I went through great pains
to create this barrier.

00:50.517 --> 00:53.854
So I can't impose restrictions
that are too unreasonable.

00:54.454 --> 00:57.291
Anyone who was inside
the barrier when I created it

00:57.391 --> 00:59.693
has the right
to leave it if they want.

01:00.794 --> 01:02.296
But just once,

01:03.063 --> 01:04.464
if you wish right now,

01:04.564 --> 01:07.234
you could wake up
outside the barrier.

01:08.835 --> 01:10.037
Would you like to do that?

01:10.504 --> 01:12.839
[SASAKI]
Wake up outside the barrier?

01:13.540 --> 01:15.309
Is this a dream?

01:16.243 --> 01:20.213
The space between dreams
and reality is a curse.

01:25.185 --> 01:26.653
So be careful.

01:26.753 --> 01:28.355
Easy, take it slowly.

01:28.889 --> 01:32.259
The most impatient ones
are already outside waiting.

01:33.060 --> 01:34.728
[footsteps]

01:52.012 --> 01:53.547
[birds chirping]

01:59.219 --> 02:00.387
Oh, right.

02:00.487 --> 02:02.556
I nearly forgot
to tell you this.

02:04.091 --> 02:06.226
Thank you for being friends
with my son.

02:06.326 --> 02:07.594
I appreciate it.

02:08.328 --> 02:09.629
[IGUCHI] Sasaki!

02:10.130 --> 02:11.264
Sasaki!

02:11.632 --> 02:13.200
- Sasaki!
- [gasps]

02:14.301 --> 02:15.502
[SASAKI] Iguchi!

02:15.602 --> 02:16.603
[sighs]

02:16.703 --> 02:19.606
I'm so glad
to see someone I know.

02:22.943 --> 02:24.378
Where are we?

02:24.911 --> 02:28.281
Somewhere between Kotodai
and Hirose Street.

02:28.782 --> 02:30.083
Never mind that. Look.

02:30.183 --> 02:31.518
What's your opinion,

02:32.052 --> 02:33.553
as an occult club member?

02:34.054 --> 02:35.322
Wow, uh...

02:35.922 --> 02:37.257
[exhales]

02:41.495 --> 02:43.630
Can I tell you
about a dream I had?

02:44.131 --> 02:45.298
[IGUCHI] We all had it.

02:45.399 --> 02:47.968
A guy with long hair
and a kasaya, right?

02:48.068 --> 02:49.036
Yeah!

02:49.469 --> 02:51.338
Did he also thank you for
being friends with his son?

02:51.438 --> 02:54.408
Mm. No, that's the first time
I heard about that.

02:58.779 --> 02:59.780
Itadori?

03:03.216 --> 03:05.419
[♪ opening theme song playing]

04:33.573 --> 04:34.908
[KINJI] For real?!

04:35.008 --> 04:37.144
Someone was able to seal Gojo?

04:37.244 --> 04:38.678
[PANDA, MEGUMI, YUJI] For real.

04:41.214 --> 04:42.749
[KINJI] Damn!

04:42.849 --> 04:45.285
Also, this might be a bad time
to tell you this,

04:45.385 --> 04:47.053
but the principal is dead.

04:51.958 --> 04:53.293
How long have you known?

04:53.393 --> 04:55.228
I'm sorry
for not telling you sooner,

04:55.328 --> 04:56.730
but it's true.

04:57.364 --> 04:59.232
It's all right though, Itadori.

04:59.332 --> 05:00.500
It wasn't in Shibuya.

05:00.600 --> 05:02.769
He fought
with the higher-ups after that.

05:03.570 --> 05:05.972
Well, that doesn't
make it any better, you know.

05:06.072 --> 05:08.575
I mean, after all,
the principal was like your--

05:08.675 --> 05:11.878
Yeah, that's what I meant by,
"It's all right, Itadori."

05:11.978 --> 05:12.946
But that's nice of you.

05:13.580 --> 05:15.682
Well, if you say
you're all right, then fine.

05:15.782 --> 05:17.317
There's nothing more
for us to add.

05:17.417 --> 05:18.552
Yeah.

05:19.553 --> 05:21.354
Still, you're talking
about everyone

05:21.454 --> 05:22.956
who's ever been good to me.

05:23.356 --> 05:24.691
I haven't been this bummed out

05:24.791 --> 05:27.961
since I watched Yakul get shot
in the ass with an arrow.

05:28.061 --> 05:30.330
[PANDA, MEGUMI, YUJI]
What a nice life you've lived.

05:30.697 --> 05:31.865
[KINJI] All right, then,

05:31.965 --> 05:34.734
I'm gonna help you all
stop this Culling Game.

05:34.834 --> 05:36.770
- [Megumi sighs]
- [Yuji chuckles]

05:37.270 --> 05:38.572
[KINJI]
Don't get me wrong, though.

05:38.672 --> 05:40.840
I'm not doing this
out of sympathy.

05:42.542 --> 05:44.211
We're cutting a deal here.

05:44.311 --> 05:45.378
Understand me?

05:45.478 --> 05:47.480
Once we clean up
this Culling Game for you,

05:47.581 --> 05:50.183
it's gonna be your turn
to help me out with something.

05:50.450 --> 05:51.885
[PANDA] You're trying
to get in on the revisions

05:51.985 --> 05:54.187
to the Jujutsu Regulations, right?

05:54.721 --> 05:57.457
Now that the existence
of curses has gone public,

05:57.557 --> 06:00.060
there's sure to be some kind
of revisions made.

06:01.628 --> 06:03.730
But what exactly
are you hoping for?

06:05.198 --> 06:06.199
[MEGUMI] Whatever it is,

06:06.499 --> 06:08.368
I doubt we'll have much trouble
doing it for you.

06:08.468 --> 06:09.402
Oh, yeah?

06:09.502 --> 06:11.171
Get a load of Sea Urchin Head.

06:11.271 --> 06:13.073
What would you know
about anything?

06:14.074 --> 06:15.141
Well...

06:15.976 --> 06:17.877
I am the new head
of the Zen'in clan.

06:19.613 --> 06:21.648
- Oh, yeah?
- Oh. Huh?

06:23.617 --> 06:25.619
[KINJI]<i>Wait, wait,
<i>wait, wait, wait, for real?</i></i>

06:25.719 --> 06:27.587
<i>Of the three crazy things
<i>I learned today,</i></i>

06:27.687 --> 06:29.256
<i>this one's the craziest!</i>

06:29.356 --> 06:31.891
<i>If I got the backing of
<i>one of the big three families,</i></i>

06:31.992 --> 06:34.060
<i>I could easily
<i>influence the revisions</i></i>

06:34.160 --> 06:35.428
<i>to the regulations.</i>

06:35.528 --> 06:37.297
<i>The only problem
<i>would come later,</i></i>

06:37.397 --> 06:38.999
<i>in trying
<i>to keep the Zen'in clan</i></i>

06:39.099 --> 06:41.534
<i>from getting involved
<i>in managing the fight club.</i></i>

06:41.635 --> 06:43.036
Sea Urchin Head!

06:43.136 --> 06:44.304
[MEGUMI] Name's Fushiguro.

06:44.404 --> 06:45.605
Fushiguro!

06:49.709 --> 06:51.645
Sorry, let's be friends.

06:51.745 --> 06:52.979
- Huh?
- [MEGUMI] Sure.

06:55.715 --> 06:59.219
Good. That just leaves deciding
who's heading to which colony.

06:59.319 --> 07:00.954
Yuta went to Miyagi, right?

07:01.054 --> 07:01.955
Ding-dong.

07:02.088 --> 07:04.691
Ding-dong, ding-dong,
ding-dong, ding-dong!

07:05.258 --> 07:06.359
Please be advised!

07:06.626 --> 07:09.429
Effective immediately,
a player has added a new rule

07:09.529 --> 07:10.864
to the Culling Game.

07:10.964 --> 07:11.731
Rule number nine.

07:11.998 --> 07:13.600
Players will know
each other's information.

07:13.700 --> 07:16.703
<i>First names, last names,
<i>number of points accumulated,</i></i>

07:16.803 --> 07:18.371
<i>current colony,
<i>and number of rules</i></i>

07:18.471 --> 07:19.973
<i>added to the game by you.</i>

07:21.007 --> 07:22.175
I am Kogane.

07:22.275 --> 07:25.545
A liaison between players
and the Culling Game.

07:25.845 --> 07:28.581
Did that thing just change
personalities halfway through?

07:28.682 --> 07:30.317
The first part
was an announcement

07:30.417 --> 07:31.518
from the Culling Game.

07:31.851 --> 07:34.721
And now, I am speaking
as the personal liaison

07:34.821 --> 07:37.691
attached to the player
Yuji Itadori.

07:39.359 --> 07:41.628
Tengen did say
something about that.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.296
It's here for you?

07:43.663 --> 07:45.532
Why is Itadori
already being counted

07:45.632 --> 07:46.833
as one of the players
in the game?

07:46.933 --> 07:49.302
Aside from those,
Kenjaku gave cursed techniques

07:49.402 --> 07:50.603
and objects to--

07:50.704 --> 07:52.739
At this point,
the only players should be those

07:52.839 --> 07:54.207
who have entered a colony.

07:55.141 --> 07:57.277
[SUGURU] There were people whom
I had absorbed cursed objects...

07:57.377 --> 07:58.812
The cursed objects
that I distributed

07:58.912 --> 08:00.080
are what's left
of the sorcerers...

08:00.347 --> 08:02.882
Of course, I forged pacts
with more than just sorcerers.

08:02.982 --> 08:05.785
<i>But he once existed as
<i>an actual human being,</i></i>

08:05.885 --> 08:07.787
<i>although it was
<i>over a thousand years ago.</i></i>

08:07.887 --> 08:10.190
- [YUJI] Sukuna.
- [KINJI] Sukuna?

08:10.623 --> 08:12.292
Sukuna was one of the sorcerers

08:12.392 --> 08:15.462
that forged a pact with Kenjaku
to become cursed objects.

08:16.062 --> 08:17.797
[MEGUMI]
<i>I bet Culling Game participation</i>

08:17.897 --> 08:19.733
<i>was included in their pact.</i>

08:19.833 --> 08:21.568
Things still aren't adding up.

08:21.835 --> 08:24.537
You swallowed Sukuna's finger
of your own free will.

08:24.637 --> 08:26.239
I witnessed it.

08:26.339 --> 08:27.574
[gasps]

08:29.109 --> 08:30.910
Hmm. Table that.

08:31.611 --> 08:32.645
Itadori,

08:33.079 --> 08:35.648
can you have Kogane pull up
the players' information for me?

08:37.283 --> 08:39.152
Kogane, can you?

08:39.252 --> 08:40.754
Sure can!

08:40.987 --> 08:42.021
Ta-da!

08:45.792 --> 08:47.127
Take a look at this guy.

08:47.660 --> 08:50.196
So he originally had 200 points?

08:50.663 --> 08:53.032
I wonder what he was
hoping for by adding a rule.

08:53.366 --> 08:55.201
[YUJI] At the very least,
he must have killed

08:55.301 --> 08:57.103
about 40 people, right?

08:57.203 --> 08:59.739
Whatever the reason,
we can assume it wasn't nice.

08:59.839 --> 09:01.341
It can still help.

09:01.441 --> 09:02.475
We could use the player's info

09:02.575 --> 09:03.777
to progress
through the Culling Game

09:03.877 --> 09:05.345
without killing anyone.

09:05.912 --> 09:08.615
Kogane, can you show me
a list of the players

09:08.715 --> 09:10.383
with 100 points or more?

09:10.650 --> 09:14.320
Sorry, I am attached
to the player, Yuji Itadori.

09:14.421 --> 09:15.889
[YUJI] Oh. No, he can use you.

09:15.989 --> 09:17.824
Just do whatever he asks.

09:19.959 --> 09:22.729
Unless someone's in a rush
to escape the barrier,

09:22.829 --> 09:25.098
like Tsumiki,
who got caught up in it,

09:25.665 --> 09:27.434
the reincarnated sorcerers

09:27.534 --> 09:29.402
must have forged
pacts with Kenjaku

09:29.502 --> 09:30.804
for their own reasons.

09:30.904 --> 09:33.873
So they're not necessarily
motivated to make this move.

09:34.140 --> 09:35.608
Therefore,
if there's anyone else

09:35.708 --> 09:38.344
with an excess of 100 points
like Kashimo...

09:38.445 --> 09:39.446
That's right.

09:39.946 --> 09:41.414
Those with 100 points,

09:41.514 --> 09:43.216
and no intention
of adding a rule.

09:43.316 --> 09:45.118
Yeah, we can lean on them.

09:45.218 --> 09:46.052
And make them add a rule

09:46.152 --> 09:48.655
to let Tsumiki
escape the Culling Game.

09:48.755 --> 09:49.923
Here you go.

09:51.958 --> 09:53.193
[MEGUMI] There's another one.

09:53.293 --> 09:54.094
- All right!
- Yes!

09:54.594 --> 09:57.497
First, we'll take advantage
of the Rule Eight obstacle.

09:57.597 --> 09:58.565
Huh?

09:58.698 --> 10:00.900
Remind me
what Rule Eight was again?

10:01.234 --> 10:03.102
[MEGUMI]<i>Players who
<i>don't show a change in points</i></i>

10:03.203 --> 10:04.237
<i>within 19 days</i>

10:04.337 --> 10:06.172
<i>shall be stripped
<i>of their technique.</i></i>

10:06.272 --> 10:08.174
<i>It's the rule
<i>that leads to death.</i></i>

10:08.475 --> 10:10.009
<i>So we add a rule that says,</i>

10:10.109 --> 10:12.445
<i>"It is now possible
<i>for players to transfer points</i></i>

10:12.545 --> 10:13.546
<i>among each other."</i>

10:14.347 --> 10:17.116
<i>That way, if they keep passing
<i>points amongst themselves,</i></i>

10:17.217 --> 10:20.186
<i>they can avoid being stripped
<i>of their techniques and dying.</i></i>

10:20.987 --> 10:22.589
Then we add one more.

10:22.689 --> 10:24.457
<i>The rule will sound
<i>something like,</i></i>

10:24.557 --> 10:26.025
<i>"If players spend enough points,</i>

10:26.125 --> 10:27.927
<i>it will allow them to
<i>leave the Culling Game."</i></i>

10:28.027 --> 10:29.929
But that would conflict
with the rule

10:30.029 --> 10:32.499
about the continuation
of the game, wouldn't it?

10:32.599 --> 10:34.200
Then we find a workaround.

10:34.300 --> 10:35.668
How 'bout we add some kind

10:35.768 --> 10:37.403
of flexible condition
to the rule?

10:37.504 --> 10:40.540
Like dragging in a non-player
to the game to take their place?

10:40.640 --> 10:41.875
[KINJI] That could work.

10:41.975 --> 10:44.110
Would Kogane be
making the call on that?

10:44.377 --> 10:47.213
[YUJI] Either way,
we know what we need to do now.

10:47.714 --> 10:48.648
[MEGUMI] Yeah.

10:49.516 --> 10:50.984
<i>While we're searching
<i>for the Angel to break</i></i>

10:51.084 --> 10:52.685
<i>the Prison Realm's seal...</i>

10:53.786 --> 10:55.855
we'll look for Hajime Kashimo

10:56.689 --> 10:57.957
and Hiromi Higuruma...

10:58.791 --> 11:00.126
<i>and hunt them down.</i>

11:02.395 --> 11:05.665
Yeah, I'm not seeing an "Angel"
anywhere on this list.

11:06.032 --> 11:07.934
[PANDA] That's probably
not her real name.

11:08.034 --> 11:10.069
Just like you're not listed
as Sukuna.

11:10.169 --> 11:11.204
[Yuji grumbles]

11:11.304 --> 11:13.873
[MEGUMI] Tengen said
she was in eastern Tokyo.

11:14.908 --> 11:16.643
That would mean
Colony Number Two, then.

11:17.176 --> 11:19.345
[KINJI] You guys know
what she looks like?

11:19.746 --> 11:21.648
Apparently,
we'll know her when we see her.

11:21.748 --> 11:23.783
That sounds like a load of crap.

11:23.883 --> 11:25.818
But okay, whatever, I guess.

11:25.919 --> 11:27.854
Panda and I will
take Tokyo Number Two.

11:27.954 --> 11:29.923
Fushiguro and Itadori,
Number One,

11:30.023 --> 11:32.425
and Kirara,
standby outside the barriers.

11:32.525 --> 11:34.294
- Why?
- [KINJI] 'Cause I said so.

11:34.827 --> 11:35.862
[PANDA] What's your reasoning?

11:35.962 --> 11:37.063
Just going by points,

11:37.163 --> 11:38.965
this Kashimo's
the strongest one,

11:39.065 --> 11:40.967
so it makes sense
for me to take him on.

11:41.067 --> 11:42.635
Mm, it’s not fair I'm left out.

11:42.735 --> 11:44.170
[KINJI] Panda,
you've got a keen nose,

11:44.270 --> 11:46.472
so focus on
sniffing out the Angel.

11:46.573 --> 11:48.608
The fact that we haven't
already heard from Okkotsu

11:48.708 --> 11:52.011
means we probably can't use
cell phones inside the barriers.

11:52.111 --> 11:54.314
So that's why we need
someone keeping tabs

11:54.414 --> 11:55.715
on what's going on outside.

11:55.815 --> 11:57.116
[sighs] Fine.

11:57.216 --> 11:58.184
Wait a minute.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.820
It might be better for me
and Fushiguro to split up.

12:00.920 --> 12:02.922
- 'Cause if Sukuna--
- Shut up.

12:03.523 --> 12:04.624
"Shut up"?

12:04.958 --> 12:07.393
None of the older students
can change the roles they got.

12:07.794 --> 12:09.162
So quit being selfish.

12:09.262 --> 12:10.330
I'm being selfish?

12:10.630 --> 12:12.498
I'm the one
worrying about you here!

12:12.865 --> 12:15.268
Oh, man, how many times
do I have to listen to this?

12:15.368 --> 12:17.904
It's a played excuse.
And a waste of time.

12:18.004 --> 12:19.372
- Yeah?!
- Yeah!

12:19.472 --> 12:21.107
You gonna fight or dance?

12:22.875 --> 12:24.410
Hello, I am Kogane!

12:24.510 --> 12:28.114
Taking place inside this barrier
is the Culling Game,

12:28.214 --> 12:30.149
where players fight
to the death!

12:30.249 --> 12:32.051
Once you decide to step inside,

12:32.151 --> 12:33.987
you, too, become a player.

12:34.087 --> 12:37.490
Are you still willing to enter
and risk everything you have?

12:37.590 --> 12:38.658
- Yeah!
- Hmm!

12:38.758 --> 12:39.993
Let's go.

12:43.796 --> 12:45.932
[HANYU]<i>Hanyu to Amai.</i>

12:47.767 --> 12:49.969
<i>I keep waiting for your signal.</i>

12:50.470 --> 12:52.171
[AMAI] Uh, well, I hear you,

12:52.272 --> 12:54.173
but there's no signal to give.

12:54.273 --> 12:56.676
I can't do much
if no one shows up.

12:57.076 --> 12:58.411
- [HANYU] What?
- [gasps]

12:59.012 --> 13:00.413
That little punk.

13:00.813 --> 13:03.149
- Mouthing off to me now?
- [thuds]

13:03.249 --> 13:05.051
No! Please.

13:05.151 --> 13:07.220
Look, I'm sorry, really!

13:08.054 --> 13:10.423
[HANYU] If you're
getting all high and mighty...

13:12.425 --> 13:13.559
I'll pull you down.

13:13.660 --> 13:14.661
[♪ thrilling music playing]

13:14.894 --> 13:16.296
[MEGUMI] We need
to be careful of the sorcerers

13:16.396 --> 13:17.163
who've reincarnated.

13:17.263 --> 13:18.931
[YUJI] My thoughts exactly.

13:19.866 --> 13:22.268
But just in case I've forgotten,
explain again.

13:22.368 --> 13:23.302
[frustrated sigh]

13:23.403 --> 13:25.905
Some of them are
from 1,000 years ago.

13:26.005 --> 13:27.540
Just 100
or 200 years ago,

13:27.640 --> 13:29.375
they valued life way less.

13:29.776 --> 13:31.110
Plus, they're sorcerers.

13:31.210 --> 13:33.212
<i>Fighting and death
<i>are common for them.</i></i>

13:33.312 --> 13:35.281
<i>Some may want to die fighting.</i>

13:35.381 --> 13:38.418
<i>That might even be why
<i>they forged a pact with Kenjaku.</i></i>

13:38.785 --> 13:42.321
I’ll bet that Higuruma
and Kashimo are past sorcerers.

13:42.722 --> 13:44.424
Don't expect fair negotiations.

13:44.524 --> 13:47.427
So then, other attacks
come from cursed spirits?

13:47.894 --> 13:49.262
[MEGUMI] Especially at night.

13:49.696 --> 13:52.465
Now, if there are modern-day
sorcerers dragged into this

13:52.565 --> 13:53.766
like Tsumiki was,

13:54.000 --> 13:54.967
they might actually be open

13:55.068 --> 13:57.070
to exchanging
information with us.

13:58.971 --> 14:01.040
Hello, my name is Kogane!

14:01.140 --> 14:04.143
Taking place inside this barrier
is the Culling Game,

14:04.243 --> 14:06.012
where players fight
to the death.

14:06.112 --> 14:09.248
Once you decide to step inside,
you, too, become a player!

14:09.349 --> 14:12.719
Are you still willing to enter
and risk everything you have?

14:13.086 --> 14:15.288
Yeah. Let's do this.

14:16.923 --> 14:18.291
Megumi Fushiguro has now

14:18.391 --> 14:20.093
officially joined
the Culling Game.

14:20.193 --> 14:21.994
Would you like
to see the rules first?

14:22.095 --> 14:24.864
- [MEGUMI] No need, I'm good.
- Boo.

14:24.964 --> 14:26.232
- [MEGUMI] Itadori?
- [YUJI] Hmm?

14:26.332 --> 14:29.135
First, we have to gather
information on Higuruma.

14:29.635 --> 14:31.104
- Ready for this?
- Yeah!

14:34.941 --> 14:36.509
[gasping]

14:36.943 --> 14:38.277
Fushiguro's gone?

14:38.711 --> 14:39.779
[NARRATOR]<i>When a player enters</i>

14:39.879 --> 14:41.814
<i>one of
<i>the Culling Game's barriers,</i></i>

14:41.914 --> 14:43.116
<i>they're randomly teleported</i>

14:43.216 --> 14:45.518
<i>to one of nine
<i>designated locations</i></i>

14:45.618 --> 14:47.053
<i>where they will begin the game.</i>

14:47.153 --> 14:49.555
<i>It was a rule
<i>of the barriers, not included</i></i>

14:49.655 --> 14:52.125
<i>in the general rules
<i>of the Culling Game.</i></i>

14:52.225 --> 14:55.328
<i>And others were waiting
<i>in those nine locations.</i></i>

14:55.628 --> 14:56.395
[AMAI] Here's one!

14:56.829 --> 14:58.865
[NARRATOR]<i>There's a name
<i>for players who target those</i></i>

14:58.965 --> 15:01.701
<i>disoriented by this
<i>unmentioned phenomenon.</i></i>

15:02.034 --> 15:03.202
[Yuji grunts]

15:03.503 --> 15:04.604
[glass shatters]

15:05.905 --> 15:07.173
[glass explodes, shatters]

15:10.843 --> 15:12.445
[NARRATOR]<i>Newbie-hunters.</i>

15:14.013 --> 15:15.281
[HANYU]
<i>He's tougher than I thought.</i>

15:15.615 --> 15:17.717
<i>That would have
<i>pulverized most guys.</i></i>

15:17.817 --> 15:19.352
<i>But he's still kicking.</i>

15:19.819 --> 15:21.587
<i>He's no ordinary person.</i>

15:22.588 --> 15:23.589
[explosion]

15:26.926 --> 15:29.095
[gasping]

15:31.430 --> 15:33.733
Darling,
let's meet up, shall we?

15:33.833 --> 15:35.334
- [whizzes, thuds]
- [groans]

15:36.636 --> 15:37.336
[thuds]

15:37.436 --> 15:39.105
[YUJI]<i>She fell pretty easily.</i>

15:39.205 --> 15:41.174
<i>I need to ask her
<i>about Higuruma.</i></i>

15:41.274 --> 15:43.142
<i>Then I have to find Fushiguro.</i>

15:43.242 --> 15:44.410
[propeller whirring]

15:44.510 --> 15:45.678
[MAN] Hanyu!

15:46.112 --> 15:49.148
What the hell did you do
to my woman?!

15:49.715 --> 15:51.184
Guess I can just ask him.

15:51.551 --> 15:54.153
[AMAI]<i>Oh, no.
<i>Now Haba flew in.</i></i>

15:54.253 --> 15:56.455
<i>Does that mean
<i>Hanyu was taken out?</i></i>

15:56.856 --> 15:59.559
<i>I think I've seen
<i>that guy before.</i></i>

15:59.792 --> 16:00.927
Itadori?

16:01.160 --> 16:02.895
[WOMAN] Ow, that hurt!

16:02.995 --> 16:04.730
Why did you do that to me?

16:04.831 --> 16:06.999
I don't even know
if I can stand.

16:07.567 --> 16:09.635
Hey, you're the one
who attacked me.

16:09.735 --> 16:10.536
<i>Damn it!</i>

16:10.803 --> 16:13.039
<i>I didn't expect us
<i>to get separated that way.</i></i>

16:13.706 --> 16:14.707
Anything?

16:15.808 --> 16:17.243
<i>Nue can't find him either.</i>

16:17.677 --> 16:20.112
<i>This colony must be
<i>larger than Shibuya.</i></i>

16:20.479 --> 16:22.782
<i>We're probably
<i>over two kilometers apart.</i></i>

16:23.316 --> 16:25.151
<i>But we both know where to head.</i>

16:26.552 --> 16:28.788
Do you know a sorcerer
named Higuruma?

16:29.255 --> 16:30.923
[WOMAN] You men are all alike.

16:31.023 --> 16:32.291
Thinking you could
just beat a woman

16:32.391 --> 16:34.560
- into listening to you, but--
- [MEGUMI] Answer me.

16:34.861 --> 16:36.529
Yes, I know him.

16:37.263 --> 16:38.931
Could be
a different Higuruma, though.

16:39.031 --> 16:40.867
Mine has 100 points.

16:41.334 --> 16:43.369
[MEGUMI]
That's the one. Where is he?

16:43.970 --> 16:45.104
Hmm?

16:45.471 --> 16:46.739
Oh!

16:46.973 --> 16:48.808
So that's how it is.

16:48.908 --> 16:49.976
[whizzes, crashes]

16:50.076 --> 16:52.378
[Yuji panting]

16:52.478 --> 16:53.412
[grunts]

16:55.147 --> 16:56.349
[Haba exclaims]

16:57.617 --> 17:00.286
[crashing]

17:01.220 --> 17:02.755
[HABA]<i>That damn brat!</i>

17:02.855 --> 17:05.191
<i>Amazing physical prowess though!</i>

17:08.928 --> 17:10.062
[Yuji grunts]

17:11.931 --> 17:12.999
[YUJI]
<i>I thought I'd be in trouble</i>

17:13.266 --> 17:15.234
<i>with him constantly
<i>holding higher ground</i>,</i>

17:15.334 --> 17:18.104
<i>but that propeller's
<i>his only means of attack.</i></i>

17:19.705 --> 17:20.640
[whirring]

17:27.747 --> 17:29.215
[whirring]

17:31.250 --> 17:33.452
[both grunting]

17:33.552 --> 17:34.520
[Haba groans]

17:37.657 --> 17:40.092
[YUJI]<i>He keeps trying
<i>to get close enough to kill me.</i></i>

17:40.192 --> 17:41.861
<i>I need to fight him indoors!</i>

17:41.961 --> 17:43.296
[Haba chuckles]

17:49.268 --> 17:51.237
[propeller approaching]

17:56.375 --> 17:58.411
You're about to be a smoothie!

18:00.646 --> 18:02.481
[YUJI]<i>He's turned
<i>his head towards me.</i></i>

18:02.581 --> 18:03.583
<i>This is it!</i>

18:05.318 --> 18:06.619
<i>That woman from earlier</i>,

18:06.752 --> 18:09.355
<i>she was sturdy enough to smash
<i>through buildings with me,</i></i>

18:09.455 --> 18:11.691
<i>but a simple thrown object
<i>made her fall.</i></i>

18:12.391 --> 18:14.894
<i>I bet their hair is the key
<i>to their cursed techniques.</i></i>

18:14.994 --> 18:17.863
<i>The further away from the hair,
<i>the less sturdy they are.</i></i>

18:17.964 --> 18:19.332
<i>How'd they become this way?</i>

18:19.432 --> 18:20.733
<i>Was it part of a pact?</i>

18:20.833 --> 18:23.202
<i>But no matter
<i>how tough their hair is,</i></i>

18:23.302 --> 18:25.404
<i>it's still attached
<i>to their heads!</i></i>

18:25.504 --> 18:27.907
[groaning]

18:29.675 --> 18:31.177
[grunting]

18:33.279 --> 18:37.650
[laughing]

18:37.750 --> 18:39.318
Broke your fist, huh?

18:39.418 --> 18:42.355
That's too bad!
'Cause you just lost this batt--

18:42.455 --> 18:44.857
- [thud]
- [groans]

18:46.659 --> 18:49.729
[groans]

18:51.430 --> 18:54.333
I didn't break anything,
it's just a scratch. Ow.

18:54.567 --> 18:56.769
[WOMAN] I don't mind telling you
where to find Higuruma,

18:56.869 --> 18:59.538
but I want you
to do me a favor in return.

19:01.173 --> 19:02.541
Spit it out.

19:02.642 --> 19:03.809
Magic word?

19:03.909 --> 19:05.011
Say "please."

19:05.111 --> 19:06.645
Or "thank you."

19:06.746 --> 19:07.713
- Or--
- Tell me.

19:08.748 --> 19:09.949
Fine.

19:11.517 --> 19:15.688
- Will you be my knight, please?
- Sure. That's fine.

19:17.156 --> 19:19.291
Oh, you're no fun at all,
are you?

19:19.392 --> 19:21.127
I don't have time for this.

19:21.227 --> 19:22.228
So hurry up.

19:22.328 --> 19:23.295
And walk in front.

19:23.396 --> 19:25.364
Do you even know
what a knight is?

19:25.698 --> 19:28.134
My knight is supposed
to protect me with his life,

19:28.234 --> 19:29.568
if necessary.

19:30.436 --> 19:32.972
[MEGUMI] I will, if you're
telling me the truth.

19:34.974 --> 19:36.675
Hey, wake up.

19:36.976 --> 19:40.379
I wanna ask you about
a sorcerer named Higuruma.

19:40.479 --> 19:41.747
- [approaching footsteps]
- Hmm?

19:42.248 --> 19:44.717
[AMAI] I... I... Itadori?

19:45.818 --> 19:46.952
I know him.

19:48.054 --> 19:49.655
That Higuruma guy.

19:50.690 --> 19:52.291
[MEGUMI] You know
what'll happen...

19:53.726 --> 19:54.960
if you're lying.

19:55.494 --> 19:57.163
<i>I'm not like Itadori.</i>

19:57.430 --> 20:00.399
<i>I'm willing to earn those
<i>100 points on my own.</i></i>

20:00.499 --> 20:02.435
[WOMAN] You know,
I do have a name.

20:02.535 --> 20:04.637
And that name is Remi.

20:04.737 --> 20:05.971
It's been a while.

20:06.072 --> 20:07.339
Do you remember me?

20:08.307 --> 20:09.608
Who are you?

20:09.975 --> 20:11.577
<i>How does he know my name?</i>

20:12.044 --> 20:13.079
Oh, sorry.

20:13.245 --> 20:15.448
I guess it was just me
who knew about you.

20:15.548 --> 20:17.983
I mean,
you're famous, after all.

20:18.084 --> 20:19.452
Tiger of West Middle.

20:19.552 --> 20:22.555
No way! You're from my hometown?
Uh... [sighs]

20:23.656 --> 20:26.258
[MEGUMI] So you're saying you're
not a sorcerer from the past?

20:26.358 --> 20:27.293
[footsteps]

20:27.827 --> 20:31.263
Why? Do these clothes
look old fashioned?

20:31.363 --> 20:33.966
And what’s your rationale
for attacking me?

20:34.733 --> 20:35.768
Listen, you.

20:36.068 --> 20:38.637
A whole lot of average people
who weren't players

20:38.738 --> 20:40.840
suddenly got let out
of the colony.

20:41.273 --> 20:42.274
But the players like me,

20:42.374 --> 20:44.176
who were in the colony
from the start,

20:44.276 --> 20:46.112
have had to participate
in the Culling Game

20:46.212 --> 20:47.880
for 12 days already!

20:48.214 --> 20:50.349
I'm not doing this
because I want to!

20:50.449 --> 20:52.852
Out here,
it's kill or be killed!

20:55.154 --> 20:58.157
You can get killed while trying
to find a reason to fight.

20:58.657 --> 21:00.860
12 days out here
has taught me that.

21:00.960 --> 21:04.230
I've seen plenty of people
drown in their power so far.

21:04.663 --> 21:06.565
So stop trying
to differentiate between them

21:06.665 --> 21:08.934
as past or present sorcerers.

21:09.635 --> 21:11.770
[MEGUMI]<i>So the sorcerers
<i>from the past have inspired</i></i>

21:11.871 --> 21:14.807
<i>the modern-day sorcerers
<i>to go into battle mode.</i></i>

21:15.374 --> 21:17.943
<i>In that case,
<i>I gave Itadori bad advice.</i></i>

21:18.410 --> 21:19.378
You sure?

21:19.478 --> 21:21.013
What about those other two?

21:21.113 --> 21:22.181
You were allies, right?

21:22.281 --> 21:24.416
[AMAI] Nah,
I was just their gofer.

21:24.517 --> 21:26.485
They would have killed me
at some point.

21:26.819 --> 21:27.753
[MEGUMI] Wait.

21:28.888 --> 21:29.989
Enough blind following.

21:30.356 --> 21:31.323
Tell me where we're going.

21:31.423 --> 21:33.192
[REMI] No way, pal.

21:33.292 --> 21:34.927
What guarantee do I have
you won't kill me

21:35.027 --> 21:37.463
right after I tell you
where to find Higuruma?

21:37.730 --> 21:38.764
Oh, I see.

21:38.864 --> 21:39.798
Uh...

21:40.065 --> 21:41.901
[AMAI] It’s Amai. Rin Amai.

21:42.134 --> 21:44.904
What am I supposed to do
if you die before we get there?

21:45.004 --> 21:46.272
[REMI] That's why!

21:46.372 --> 21:48.974
I need you to be my knight
and protect me!

21:49.074 --> 21:50.509
And use my name already!

21:50.609 --> 21:51.844
Just covering my bases.

21:51.944 --> 21:54.847
Amai, where exactly
can I find Higuruma?

21:54.947 --> 21:56.015
[REMI] Okay, fine.

21:56.115 --> 21:58.250
I'll give you a rough idea
of where we're going.

21:58.350 --> 21:59.485
[AMAI]
The stronger people are gathered

21:59.585 --> 22:01.220
in what used to be
the heart of the city.

22:01.320 --> 22:02.588
It's where
most of the supplies are.

22:02.855 --> 22:04.924
- [REMI] Higuruma's in...
- [AMAI] Higuruma's in...

22:05.024 --> 22:06.492
- Ikebukuro.
- Shinjuku.

22:06.592 --> 22:08.127
- Got it?
- Got it?

22:10.296 --> 22:12.531
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:40.619 --> 23:43.489
[HIROMI]<i>I sense much
<i>potential in the Culling Game.</i></i>

23:43.589 --> 23:45.491
[YUJI]<i>Every person
<i>in this nation will die.</i></i>

23:45.591 --> 23:46.792
[REGGIE]<i>I'm sorry,</i>

23:47.026 --> 23:48.894
- <i>but she deceived you.
- [AMAI]<i>I'm sorry, Itadori.</i></i>

23:48.994 --> 23:51.030
[MEGUMI]<i>A sorcerer
<i>connected to Kenjaku?</i></i>

23:51.130 --> 23:51.830
[YUJI]<i>I wanna talk.</i>

23:51.931 --> 23:53.766
[HIROMI]<i>We're having a retrial.</i>
